        This is the first iteration of Interpost v2, built with Strapi and Astro.

        Strapi is an open-source headless CMS, it allowed me to build a solid content layout in no time.
        I then consume the Strapi API with Astro, a brand new static site generator featuring all the latest trends in 
        terms of frontend tooling: 
        - Bundled with Vite, offering insane HMR speed and build times.
        - Can support any frontend framework, from React to Vue with Svelte, Preact and Lit.
        - Innovative templating technique, kind of a hybrid between FrontMatter, Svelte and JSX.

        Strapi is configured in a very standard way, but working with Astro has been very interesting since it has a
        very innovative way of allowing the developer to use their favorite language. In my case, I built a theme switcher
        using Svelte.

        The detailed tech stack is
        - Backend: Strapi
        - API: GraphQL
        - Frontend: Astro with Svelte renderer
        - CSS: Pico
        - Hosting: backend --> Heroku, frontend --> Netlify, media --> Cloudinary

